caption: Highly Recommend.  Came in with a group of close friends and we ordered a little bit of everything. The carrots are out of this world! Brussel sprouts tied in second place with the meatballs and the buttermilk and kale caesar salads are great items to start your meal off with!  Dinner was the lasagna for me, and it was absolutely delicious. We ordered  Bronco and Gem State of Mind pizzas for the main course And both were incredible. I imagine most of their pies will be amazing as the crust is the foundation and it is out of this world. Light, flaky, with a solid crisp that comes from the cooking... They also have a wonderful selection of whisky and the bar staff is delightful as well.
Fantastic food and great service!
Incredible pizza, comparable to pizzas I've had in italy!
Visiting here from Cali. Was referred here. Glad we came. Supper Friendly employees. If you like pizza the crust and toppings are amazing. Great atmosphere .
OMG

The atmosphere inside and outside the building is great.  There's A very upscale feel while at the same time being very inviting.  Our servers were friendly and attentive without being overbearing.  Now, about the food...  I can honestly say this is some of the best pizza I've had in the area.  We got the wings as an appetizer and they had a great brunch with a really delicious sauce.  They were so good that we didn't even need the dipping sauce.  I've been here twice now and both times I had a great experience, so I can honestly say that I intend to come here many more times.

One of our favorite spots in Boise! The salads and sandwiches are great for lunch and the pizza for dinner is equally amazing! Highly recommend the Caesar salad with crispy chicken and the Honey badger pizza!
Great pizza crust. Will definitely go back.
So yummy! Pizza and apps are on point. Service was great as well
This is some solid za
Like the take out since we are still in the middle of a pandemic. Really good pizza and to tell you the truth I haven’t had a bad thing on the menu. Cant wait to actually dine inside the place!
Real classy place. Authentic pizza, similar to being in Italy. Very cool atmosphere. Great service. Definitely coming back here.
Honey Badger is a fantastic pizza. You should also try the Farm Girl with Pepperoni!
Great food, amazing atmosphere!
Fantastic service and the pizza might be the best in town

This is a standout restaurant in Boise, for sure. We moved from a popular Southern foodie tourist destination, so we have high expectations for dining, and Wylder is our favorite restaurant in the Treasure Valley. Excellent cocktails (True Grit is our go to). Deliciously fresh salads and insanely tasty vegetable sides (we probably go back more for the vegetables than anything else 😆). And, great pizza with a fantastic sourdough base. We have been doing online ordering with curbside pickup all year and it’s been excellent. Their food holds up well on the drive home.

Wow... Just wow. Such good food and a vibrant, modern aesthetic. Excellent service, 11/10! Be prepared for a bit of a higher brow meal, but not snobby. Obviously you have to get the pizza made from 53-year-old sourdough starter!
The Wylder is a refreshing establishment with great ambiance and a delightfully unique and delicious menu.
Best pizza in town, hands down!
Kale salad is delicious. The fingerling potato was well done with a hint of lemon. Wish the staff was more friendly. Otherwise, wonderful place to eat.
Ordered a Crispy Pepperoni pizza to go today.  They said 20 minutes.  It was ready in 20 minutes.  It was THE BEST PEPPERONI PIZZA EVER!  (Trying to post a photo of this thing of beauty)
Never disappoints!!  Order all the things and share with your friends.

Service is excellent! They are very busy but was quick cleaning tables and to seat new arriving guests.  Food was amazing! Had some veggies, some appetizers, and some pizzas. Everything was exquisite!

My absolute FAVORITE restaurant in all of Boise. No matter what you order, you cannot lose! Everything is just incredible. My favorite is the pizza! Amazing service, environment, and overall experience, every time. Just love the Wylder!!
Fantastic pizza crust!

Our fav pizza place in town. Wonderful brosses sprouted salad too. Super friendly staff and somehow they even remember you. Well done. Always super accommodating for our little kid's when we used to dine in. Easy online ordering and pick up process. Wonderful. highly recommend
Had pizza and salad. Pizza had a great crust and salad a great dressing, will eat there again soon.
The most glorious white pizzas. What a treat! We got a pizza, salad and veg and all 3 were 10/10. Mmmm the gutters dressing... the crispy breadcrumbs..the charred edge stretchy dough.

My friend and I were visiting and we stopped in. We loved that they were so flexible and would let you get a half white base and a half red base pizza. We picked to do the kale and spinach with chilli flakes on white base and italian sausage and mozzarella on red sauce on the other half. It was phenomenal! Best pizza in Idaho!
Fantastic food! 53 yrs old sourdough starter for their pizza....amazing 🤤 Hanna was a gem..very knowledge about the menu.
It's the best pizza crust in town, the vibe is great, the staff is kind, and desserts are delicious.
Nice atmosphere, great food.
Mushrooms toast is a must try
Great place to eat.  Great food.  Super staff.

The Wylder is a top notch restaurant in downtown Boise. The food is always great and the ambience is just as good. I would highly recommend the mushroom toast as an appetizer and the true grit on the drink menu.

The perfect spot for delicious food/drinks and amazing hospitality in a environment that is comfortable, refined and taking Covid protocols seriously.  After a 12 hour drive from Zion on our way home to Portland, The Wylder and their gracious team made for the perfect destination dinner and very reasonably priced for super high quality food, drinks and precision execution.  Love this spot!
Recently back for Thanksgiving I ate at Wylder with my buddy and hands-down the pizza was amazing, the beer was great and the service excellent.
I think this is the best pizza I’ve ever had.
Tasty salads, pizza and cocktails! Yum - we’ll definitely be back.
Always excellent food and service

My husband and I and our little one headed to this spot, one we've been eyeballing for a while now. With the location perfect for those staying in the hotels, walkable to a whole lot, definitely head here! We had a few tasty treats, meatballs, cauliflower, and the mushroom pizza plus some wine and the RB "Gin"sburg, which was divine!!! Beyond the exceptional food, which was flavorful and delicious, the service was brilliant. Having a one year at old who is very active makes dinner out at decent restaurants a toss up. The staff here went above and beyond to make sure that we had what we needed, offering to hold our kiddo for a bit as she had ants in her pants, and when we moved outside where her adventurous self could scramble and climb all over, they turned on the heaters and moved all our food with genuine care. They are the true gems! From manager to server to hostess, each and every one of them took care of us beyond the normal experience. Seriously amazing humans! Thank you for letting us have a good dinner out at a classy place and accommodating our wild child.

Wowow every experience I've had with these guys has been above and beyond! Both take out and sit down service. It's clear this restaurant and all of their staff works together so so well and this shows in the quality of service that they provide! Not to mention the menu is fantastic and the vibe lovely. One of my favorite spots in Boise hands down!
The cheese was so creamy and the crust was crispy. Such amazing flavors.
An experience in dining. We love this place! Order the honey badger pizza and any of the veggie plates. Chef’s kiss ;-*
A dining staple in Boise. Consistently going above and beyond for every table and some of the best pizza ever.  Lasagna is to dieeee for!
1st time here. Very very good. Had the mushroom toast and french picnic
Great pizza! Fresh concept on non ordinary pizza.
Couldn't ask for more

Every.single.thing we ordered was delicious. We started with yummy cocktails with clever names and the mushroom toast. Do not hesitate to order the mushroom toast- it was AMAZING. We ordered a salad and a pizza to share which we enjoyed. We even had leftovers! We rarely order dessert, but everything was so good that we wanted to try it, and were not disappointed! The ice cream pie was scrumptious to the last bite. The staff was delightful too. Service is complicated right now (due to Covid restrictions) but they killed it. We highly recommend The Wylder.
Always great service, always great food, always happy we came.
Fantastic, amazing food and great service.
Amazing food! Inventive salads, delicious pizza. A great place to share a meal with friends!
Delicious pizza and excellent service! Very fresh ingredients, some of the best wood-fired pizza we’ve had!
Very good pizza. The every night salad was literally to die for. Very fresh. Kind of limited menu, but a lovely little environment.
Favorite place in Boise. Went there two nights in a row!!
Excellent pizza, apps, and cocktails. Friendly service and dogs welcome at their outdoor seating!
Food was amazing. We had the fried chicken and also a pizza .  Also the server was great.  She made  sure our tea was never empty and was so friendly I just wish I could remember her name .
real food real people really good!
Great pizza.
Great service. Good food. Sourdough pizza crust. Nice!!!!

Great place if you want the most expensive pizza you’ll ever buy and $10 bucks for a handful of Roman and a couple of apple slices. You pay for the atmosphere and social time but if you want take out spend that hard earned money else where. I’ve never spent $55 on pizza salad and 2 lemonades and will never do so again.

Headed downtown after work with my boss and met up here. We had the honey badger pizza and couldn't get enough.  Best pizza i've ever had and the staff were attentive and very friendly.  Highly recommend.

Was told it would be a 35 min wait, then they got us in in 15 min for outdoor seating. The veggies (we had beets and brussel sprouts) were a delicious appetizer. The pizzas were incredible too, and had lots of high-quality ingredients. 1 pizza would cover about 2 adults, so you can try a few!

Outstanding menu! Per other reviews, we ordered the honey badger pizza. We are usually not fans of white sauce based pizza but this was AMAZING. The spicy honey and caramelized onions added a sweetness that paired so well with the globs of mozzarella plus the crust was perfectly dough-ey on the inside and crispy on the outside. I would also recommend the Brussels sprouts. Super crispy and flavorful. The fried chicken sandwich was the only thing that we didn’t love. The insides were good but the bread was so tough and chewy it made it really challenging to eat so we eventually just ate the insides instead of putting up a fight with the bread. I was surprised the side offered with the sandwich was a salad or chips which seemed to be bagged, when everything else on the menu was homeade, so that’s the only reason for the knock on a star. Drinks were great!
Amazing pizza and amazing drinks!
Great food. Great service
This was our first time eating here.  Our real estate agent gave us a gift card at closing.  What a treat!  The food and service is spectacular!
Great food, atmosphere and service!

"Safe" for Gluten Sensitive folks! 53 year old sourdough starter! Whaaa? So cool. I was so impressed! The vibes were positively welcoming and happy in this place (...not easily accomplished during a pandemic at a restaurant). The management is awesome, and I can tell because it showed through all levels of customer service (on the phone, at the door, at the table, followed through by very friendly manager presence). Kale and Chanel were so wonderful (and informative)! The pizza was mind-blowing delicious! The ingredients were so flavorful and fresh; I immediately trusted the menu and sourcing of ingredients. They were having a Neighborhood Special - pizza and a bottle of wine for $30. And they allow you to do 1/2 & 1/2, so I tried the Margherita, the Pepperoni, the Purple Kale one, and the Mushroom Party that I added crumbled sausage to (my favorite). ALL so good! I cannot wait to go back! Thanks for being amazingly resilient amidst the adversity of today. I appreciate the entire Wylder team; you got my vote.
Amazingly delicious pizza.
Everything I had, the food and drinks, uhhmazing. I have been there a few times and it is amazing every single time. And the environment and service was also impeccable.
5 star food with 3 star service.
After 3 months into moving back to Boise, I've finally found a good darn drink, good service and delightful food. Good god, there is hope for this town 🤞
Great food!
Love this place. Drinks are great, food is off the charts and their staff is awesome. Not sure what else you can ask for...
This is our favorite place not just because the food and cocktails are amazing but because the service is outstanding.
Loved everything!
In Boise for one night and so happy we came Here. We got the crispy Brussels sprouts, honey badger and bronco pizzas. AMAZING. Seriously so good. And we have high standards for our pizza !
Best pizza in all of downtown Boise, never disappoints and always consistent in service, quality and cleanliness of establishment. You won't be disappointed, highly recommended!!

Stopped here on our way through Boise and were EXTREMELY impressed. The wait staff was top notch, the atmosphere comfortable and chic, and the food was absolutely amazing. Be sure to get something with the lemon aioli and a side of house-made ranch. The mushroom toast is a must have. The pizza crust, perfect.
Nice joint, very friendly staff. Everything was super tasty. Will definitely be back.
Pizza needs some diversity of flavors/creativity but crust is good. Brussel sprouts good
Best pizza ever!!

A must if you’re in Boise!!! Hands down some of my favorite food I’ve had in awhile. Unbelievable app (pictured here) of ricotta and preserves. The pizza was so insanely good and reasonably priced for what you get. Staff is insanely kind, too!
Great pizza and salads. They wipe down the tables but not the menus so you should sanitize/wash your hands before you eat.

Great atmosphere and delicious food. The appetizers and pizza are really good! (they use high quality mozzarella on the pizza) But by far the best thing we had was the fried chicken dinner! I didn't expect this from a mostly pizza restaurant, but it was some of the best fried chicken I've had! Plus, the coleslaw and biscuit were fantastic. I've added Wylder to my best of Boise list.
Great atmosphere and always good service. Love the creative drinks and veggies.
The Mushroom Toast is beyond AMAZING!

Male bartender with the tattoos is an excellent addition to their staff. Knowledgeable, funny and provided great service AND great cocktails. Food was amazing, as always. Definitely one of the best spots in Boise.
Always great food and great staff.

I have really enjoyed this spot since my first visit almost 2 years ago. This time around we had the yummy meatballs as an appetizer and Lasagna and the special squash pizza for dinner. I'm not gonna lie, that pizza ranks among the top 3 pizzas I have had in my entire life!

Couldn't get any better!  We ordered the Wyld night in :)  Mushroom party pizza (my favorite) kale salad and the best brussel sprouts ever!  With a delicious bottle of red wine!  Yay!  After working all day this made my night.  My husband picked up our dinner curbside and said it was SO EASY, so double thumbs up!  He'll be our designated Wylder pick-up man.  We might order again tomorrow :)

Excellent cocktails, service, and food! The Wylder is a great place for both families and adults. The bar does great job at mixing up just about anything! I really appreciate a bar staff that can take a single ingredient suggestion,  like "I enjoy mezcal", and create a really great cocktail! The pizzas are upscale and the brussel sprouts are to die for. The sourdough crust is a huge treat too!  I never thought I'd like honey on a pizza but if you're feeling just a little adventurous give the Honey Badger a try!
Great ambiance, staff, food & bev quality but a perfectly textured pizza crust, for me, tainted by sourdough.
Love the fancy cocktails!
Love this place. clean,  and great service,  love the food.  Me and my husband do our dates here. Really fun place to go. I tell people about this place all the time
Best Pizza in Town!!!  Buttermilk Salad is delicious as well. Safe, Clean, Curbside Delivery! This is a must try!
Love the Honey Badger pizza. I picked up one on my way out of town to bring home. Home is Idaho Falls it is that good. Highly recommend it. Great customer service also.
Try the honey badger pizza 😍

Had the Mushroom pizza with Whie sauce. The pizza was a soggy mess. Salad was great, but 10 bucks for a Ceasar is a lot. Crust is OK, but there are a lot better pizza places out there for less money. 1 and done.
Great pizza and salad! Wonderful service and helpful with the menu.
Excellent food! Best pizza. We tried 4 different ones and they were all excellent.
Love love love this place!! I haven’t ordered something that I don’t like. This is our go to date night. Great staff and great food.
Healthy well prepared meals. However, the savory foods did have sweet sauces added, which should knock off 1/2 star.
Good pizza with a unique sourdough crust.  Excellent vegetables.  I liked the roasted(?) peppers especially.  Good wine & beer.  Not a "budget" place though.
Always a favorite! Love their heirloom tomato special pizza!
Love love love! Beautiful enjoyable atmosphere and great service, fabulous pizza, good wine, bread and salad. Will be back!
Two words: MUSHROOM TOAST!

Had two amazing veggie plates. The brussel sprouts are to die for! Our server, Hannah, was attentive and helpful in directing us to a place close by for a vegan dessert that was required by one in our party. Great experience!
Good Kale Caesar.
Great food, fun service!
Super quality and flavor's. Highly recommend you try!
Great Atmosphere and amazing food!

I bring everyone new to Boise here. Some of the best food I’ve eaten, everything I’ve had on the menu is DELICIOUS. Really good for a meal, really good just for drinks as well. Hint: Get the Bloody Mary.
Ughhhh those fresh veggies and the housemade ricotta tho 🤤🤤🤤

Absolutely fantastic!  Service is exemplary; food is exquisite (make sure you try the mushroom toast- even if you don't like mushrooms! It's to die for!) and atmosphere is fresh and comfortable.  One of my absolute favorites!  Lunch or dinner- YUM!!!
Pizzas are excellent. When my wife and I travel we like to try different pieces of places. Wilder certainly is among the best. Not a big menu or wine list but all is excellent.

The pizza here was amazing! We went for the Neighborhood night, which is Tuesday and Wednesday I believe. You get a bottle of the house wine, they have both a red and a white; and a pizza (any pizza you want with any amount of toppings) for $30. It's a steal! The place was trendy, the staff was nice, chipper and punctual even though every table was full. Will definitely visit again! Also there is parking right across the street!
Insanely good.  Wild mushroom toast won my heart
Loved the food and the ambiance! Went prepared to pay for parking so it made my experience much better.
Pizza is decent for Boise, but the fried chicken is the best around.
Delicious food, great cocktails and amazing atmosphere!
Pizza was excellent as well as the salads. Usually easy parking.
Love the honey badger and mushroom pizzas. Pepperoni was a little spicier than expected. Prefer white pizzas to red pizzas. Glad to have some decent pizza in Boise.

This could very well be one of our new favorite places! Went here for a work dinner (group of six) and had an amazing experience from start to finish. Amazing service. Awesome appetizers. Delicious pizza and lasagna. And super yummy dessert. All in all we loved this place. Thanks, Wylder!
I love it here. Excellent service, great food.
You: A pizza lover Wylder: The best pizza in Boise. They start with a sourdough crust, and have 10 different artisanal topping options. Great appetizers as well; go for the brussels.

The Wylder has probably the best pizza in Boise. Red Bench is really good too. Good cocktails. Nice vibe. Here's a TMI comment: 3 out the 4 us had.... uh......some intestinal distress later that evening. A coincidence I'm almost positive.
Wonderful pizza, and they will make it one half of two different types makes it twice as good.  Very good service, great casual place.

When we walked in we were told  We quit it not be C dead unless our whole party was present. There were multiple empty tables. During dinner we saw at least 4 parties being seated without their full party. What a disappointment.
Best pizza in town, dang, yum!
Pizzas and cocktails in a up scale downtown setting.
What a great addition to Boise. The food is excellent and service was great.
They know how to keep me coming back. Always great a great dinning experience!
Nice atmosphere. Very friendly staff. Excellent food. My margherita pizza was fantastic, but a tad too much salt.
I’m mad they got rid of the beet juice cocktail when they had a fresh beet salad too. Amazing restaurant. Get the kale Cesar and not any other salad. Just kale Cesar. You won’t regret it.

I've gotta agree with the consensus here - really good pizza, cordial and efficient service, good experience.   Only bummer is a longish wait, but they managed well with text alerts and a good bar.   We'll be back.
Artisan pizza with a great cocktail list. The Honey Badger is a must-try!
A very good small restaurant in downtown Boise. They make good pizza, salads, and sandwiches. The pizza dough come from a sourdough starter and is truly excellent.
Great food and atmospheric

Great wood fired pizza.red Sauce could be more flavorful with a bit of oregano.  Train bus people to ask before removing dishes, I wanted to finish my salad and never had a chance to react to stop him
Great place to hang out for weekend brunches or dinners. Very good vegan/ vegetarian options and amazing pizza! With yummy cocktails to boot, what more can you ask for?
I got a "honey badger" pizza and some brussel sprouts. Both were delicious. I think pretty much every table was full, but it didn't seem crowded and wasn't too loud. The service was great as well.
Hell yes. Monday night football with the gentle Tenders at the bar. Cheers boys.
This is the best restaurant in Boise!
Very good authentic pizza. It seemed like a hip, trendy place.

My experience at The Wylder was a study in mediocrity. After reading reviews, my wife and I were excited to try this Boise restaurant that lives off the normal paths we travel for our gastronomic adventures. We started with the Mushroom Toast and two dirty martinis. The drinks were okay; when so many people bragged about the cocktails and I have a martini with a bunch of ice chips in it, I wasn't impressed. The toast was a tasty start but the sourdough crust was almost too tough to cut with the a knife and the flavor seemed muted. At $13.00 I was worried about out entrees. My wife got the lasagna and it was good but again not the fabled thing I had read about in reviews. For the cost, a slice of a crusty, garlicky bread would have really helped to elevate it. I had the fried chicken. This is where I ran into real issues. The chicken was a touch over-cooked and boring, while my biscuit was completely raw in the middle. I have only returned food twice in my life. I try to find the bright side as much as I can, but I'm not going to pay the consequences of raw dough. My plate was taken back and while I waited several minutes, my wife finished her dinner. A new plate came out and I opened up my biscuit to find a toasty exterior with an ice cold interior. The chicken was again boring and seemed to be fried again and dry. I let the server know and the manager ended up making an effort to make it right. I appreciated that but I know that I will not be back.

Whenever we are in Boise this is our favorite spot to eat lunch or dinner. The pizzas are excellent and all the salads and sides keep things interesting! Fun cocktails and wine list also. Keep up the great work , Wylder!
Great food, great service, very quick. A little expensive, but worth it
Great pizza, but the Fried Chicken and Biscuit are the best!
Love the good and atmosphere, and they are great with kids for a nicer restaurant.  The pizzas are so yummy!
Great pizza

Very disappointing. I have heard good thing about this place. The first time we left without ordering. The owners wife chased us down to find out why and encouraged us to come back. I finally came back only to discover that the food was undercooked and over cooked. That aside the server Alyx was on point and did everything she could to resolve. I appreciate her.
Yum!!!

Me and my wife absolutely loved this little place. First off, the atmosphere inside is really comfortable and inviting. It's very clean and the staff is really friendly, the waitress paid a lot of attention to us despite the place being busy. We ordered the Margherita pizza and it was delicious. The crust is thin but not too crunchy and the flavor was just amazing. The drinks we had were also great and we both definitely will be coming back here.

Ordered several salads and pizzas - the pepperoni, margherita, and the wild gem (I think)! All were amazingly delicious - definitely compare to the pizza I had while in Italy, so I highly recommend this spot ☺️

Not bad

Then once we finally got sat down and got our food the pizza was overly greasy and the crust was flaccid. Which is ironic as the pizza ordered was a crispy pepperoni. Should be everyones first stop in Boise. Amazon staff. Elegant restaurant. Stupendous food. Try the wedge salad with salami and marinated peppers. We ate every last piece on the plate. The pizza of the day was heirloom tomatoes on goat cheeze and spinach along with an oil and garlic drizzle. But no matter how good the toppings were the crust is the real star. Cripsy on the outer and chewy on the inside. With just enough of a pillow at the end of the slice to enjoy but leaving you begging for the next slice.
I was in Boise for a work trip and we were starving. Holy yummy pizza and such a fun restaurant in the heart of Downtown.
Probably the best restaurant in town right now
The pizza and salad are amazing and they have great service.
Love this place for lunch.
So far, this was the best pizza that I have had downtown and I love the environment. A++
We had two cocktails, both were excellent. The Brussel Sprouts were outstanding and the pizza was delicious (Honey Badger). Prices are not cheap but you are getting the quality your paying for.
GR8 food. Attentive staff.

To put it into perspective, I had one slice of pizza with virtually NO cheese. Not sure how that works, but I wasn't happy I paid $17 for a pizza with minimal to no ingredients. See pics.
